)|APT]]\n* [[Arc (programming language)|Arc]]\n<!-- [[Arduino]] is an environment; the language is effectively C++ -->\n<!-- [[Arden Syntax]]<ref>http://www.openclinical.org/gmm_ardensyntax.html</ref>\n-- Arden is the syntax used in Medical Logic Module development(Also known as Arden Syntax).  S. C. Holt, 04/16/2012\n-- Arden is not a programming language, rather a formal language for encoding medical information -->\n* [[ARexx]]\n<!--* [[Arduino]] Is based on lua code not a language itself-->\n* [[Argus (programming language)|Argus]]\n<!-- ArnoldC belongs on the esoteric page -->\n<!-- [[Active Server Pages|ASP]] is an environment, not a language -->\n* [[Assembly language]]\n<!-- Asciidots belongs on the esoteric page -->\n* [[AutoHotkey]]\n* [[AutoLISP|AutoLISP / Visual LISP]]\n* [[Averest]]\n* [[AWK]]\n* [[Axum (programming language)|Axum]]\n}}\n\n== B ==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=22em|\n* [[B (programming language)|B]]\n* [[Babbage (programming language)|Babbage]]\n* [[Ballerina (programming_language)|Ballerina]]\n* [[Bash (Unix shell)|Bash]]\n* [[BASIC]]\n<!-- [[BBC Basic 256]] \u2013 see [[List of BASIC dialects]] -->\n* [[bc (programming language)|bc]]\n* [[BCPL]]\n* [[BeanShell]]\n* [[Batch file|Batch file (Windows/MS-DOS)]]\n<!-- Befunge belongs on the esoteric page --->\n* [[Bertrand (programming language)|Bertrand]]\n* [[BETA (programming language)|BETA]]\n<!-- Bungee\n[[File:Bootstrapped|thumb]]\n belongs on the esoteric page --->\n<!-- Binary is synonym for [[machine code]] -->\n* [[BLISS (programming language)|BLISS]]\n<!-- [[Blitz Basic]] \u2013 see [[List of BASIC dialects]] -->\n* [[Blockly]]\n* [[BlooP and FlooP|BlooP]]\n* [[Boo (programming language)|Boo]]\n* [[Boomerang (programming language)|Boomerang]]\n* [[Bosque (programming language)|Bosque]]\n* [[Bourne shell]] (including [[Bash (Unix shell)|bash]] and [[Korn shell|ksh]])\n<!-- [[Brainfuck]] belongs on the esoteric page -->\n<!-- [[Qualcomm Brew|BREW]] from its wiki page, it uses c/c++, no